20:27.144 --> 20:28.306
He was raised from the dead.

20:28.586 --> 20:31.230
And what is evidence of somebody being raised from the dead?

20:32.111 --> 20:34.034
He appears to people.

20:34.690 --> 20:41.679
Not only to the 12 disciples, but in the next verse that we didn't look at, verse six, appeared to a lot more people.

20:42.460 --> 20:45.123
The evidence that somebody raised from the dead is they appear.

20:45.884 --> 20:54.374
They make appearance, not just some illusion, not just in somebody's dream, but physically appeared to a lot of eyewitnesses.

20:55.976 --> 21:00.562
Actually, there's been a lot written and spoken about the resurrection of Christ.

21:00.898 --> 21:04.402
But I'll just give you one simple line of evidence that many have used in the past.

21:05.544 --> 21:17.078
The whole idea of the early church, the early believers, some of who were eyewitnesses of this whole thing, whatever, the whole idea that they would die be willing to be martyred for something they knew wasn't true.

21:17.839 --> 21:23.506
Like if Jesus wasn't really dead and didn't really was raised from the dead, the resurrection, it's like

21:23.618 --> 21:25.220
Do you really think you would die for that?

21:25.280 --> 21:31.045
I mean, if you knew it, the whole thing was just kind of a hoax where somebody just set it up, somebody came up with a nice story, whatever.

21:31.085 --> 21:36.611
You know, if you're gonna just believe something for your own beliefs, that's one thing.

21:37.331 --> 21:38.413
You're gonna die for it?

21:39.253 --> 21:40.635
You better really believe it.

21:41.275 --> 21:47.642
And so there were hundreds, thousands of people in the early church who were willing to die because it was real.

21:48.643 --> 21:50.304
Jesus really died for our sin.

21:50.805 --> 21:52.146
He was really raised from the dead.

21:52.642 --> 21:53.743
So what is the gospel?

21:54.043 --> 21:58.648
According to the Apostle Paul at 1 Corinthians 15, we've got to believe Jesus is the Son of God.

21:59.289 --> 22:00.330
He died for our sin.

22:00.910 --> 22:01.831
He rose from the dead.

22:02.652 --> 22:03.913
It really is that simple.

22:06.236 --> 22:11.581
Now, again, some of you have been around for a long time and say, wow, you know, really?

22:12.342 --> 22:14.624
We really need to hear the gospel explain to us again.

22:15.645 --> 22:20.850
Well, no matter how long we've been Christians, no matter how long we've been in church, no matter how many times we've heard these lessons,

22:21.314 --> 22:33.909
If tomorrow you're at work, or at school, in your neighborhood, and somebody says, and bought just out of the blue, or to somebody you know as a friend, whatever, and they say, what do I have to believe to become a Christian?

22:34.871 --> 22:41.419
I hope it becomes really crystal clear in our hearts and our minds from a passage like 1 Corinthians 15.

22:42.220 --> 22:43.962
What does a person have to believe to become a Christian?

22:44.542 --> 22:46.285
We've got to believe that Jesus is the Son of God.

22:46.865 --> 22:50.770
We've got to believe He died for our sin, and we've got to believe He was raised from the dead.

22:51.362 --> 22:54.506
And that's all we have to trust to become a Christian.

22:54.846 --> 22:59.131
To have the forgiveness of all of our sin and know we're going to heaven and the being with God forever.

22:59.471 --> 23:01.433
That's really how simple it is.

23:02.174 --> 23:09.983
The last thing in your outline, on your notes, this is just kind of a simple summary of the Gospel message.

23:10.984 --> 23:19.954
It's alliteration, meaning these three key words that all start with the same letter P. It's not necessarily the best way to remember it, just one way.

23:20.226 --> 23:23.109
that I've shared before, that I'll share with you again.

23:23.470 --> 23:28.295
Because sometimes it's hard to remember first Corinthians 15 and all these verses and all these concepts.

23:28.895 --> 23:30.677
Remember these three key words though.

23:31.398 --> 23:37.285
The first one is a problem, the second one is a provision, and the third is a personal decision.

23:38.226 --> 23:41.850
Problem, provision, personal decision.

23:42.590 --> 23:43.471
What's the problem?

23:44.052 --> 23:45.053
The problem of sin.

23:45.113 --> 23:49.458
And there are passages like Romans chapter three, verse 23,

23:49.890 --> 23:54.656
Romans 3, 23 says, for all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God.

23:55.396 --> 23:58.060
All have sinned and fall short of the glory of God.

23:58.080 --> 24:02.505
And if you've been around a while, you've heard me preach this many, many times, what is sin?

24:02.985 --> 24:07.811
It is not just going out and doing horrible things like robbing a bank or killing somebody or whatever.

24:07.971 --> 24:10.995
Sin is falling short of who God is.

24:11.756 --> 24:17.042
His infinite holiness, His righteousness, it's falling short of what Jesus is like.

24:17.570 --> 24:28.081
It's not just doing bad things, it's not doing all the good things that I know God would want me to do, to be more kind and forgiving and encouraging.

24:28.842 --> 24:32.005
And all the positive things that we think of when we think of Jesus.

24:32.565 --> 24:34.928
Am I like Jesus every day of my, of course not.

24:35.769 --> 24:39.853
I fall short of that every day of my life, that sin.

24:39.913 --> 24:44.978
And then Romans chapter six verse 23 says, the wages of sin is death.

24:45.154 --> 24:52.281
What I deserve for my sin is eternal separation from the almighty, holy, and loving God of the universe.

24:52.741 --> 24:53.482
That's what I deserve.

24:53.502 --> 24:54.563
That's what all of us deserve.

24:55.744 --> 25:00.749
But the free gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ.

25:01.790 --> 25:03.832
And Jesus talked about what is eternal life.

25:03.872 --> 25:04.953
It's not just living forever.

25:05.013 --> 25:06.235
Everybody's going to live forever.

25:07.416 --> 25:09.258
It's not talking about quantity of time.

25:09.278 --> 25:10.739
It's talking about quality of time.

25:11.239 --> 25:13.842
Either we're going to live forever in the loving

25:14.114 --> 25:26.246
Holy presence of God in heaven, or the Bible's clear, we will exist forever in a place of torment, where we will only experience the righteous wrath of Almighty God.

25:27.307 --> 25:40.320
Now, that's not something you hear too often, and quite frankly, to be honest, I probably don't speak up enough about the truth of God in relationship to the reality of eternal separation from Him, for unbelievers.

25:41.041 --> 25:41.842
But it's true.

25:42.018 --> 25:44.761
It's certainly not a popular message in our society today.

25:45.441 --> 25:48.384
And some people scoff at the whole idea of a literal heaven and hell.

25:49.105 --> 25:58.394
But if you believe the Bible, if you take the Bible for what it is, the Word of God, you can't come away with any other conclusion that God is talking about a literal heaven and hell.

25:59.275 --> 26:05.240
And every single person with an eternal soul is going to spend all eternity in one of those two places.

26:06.201 --> 26:11.186
So this is so, excuse me, that's why this is so important.

26:13.250 --> 26:14.011
problem of sin.

26:15.093 --> 26:17.657
We're all falling short of the glory of God.

26:17.837 --> 26:21.863
All of us are deserving of eternal separation from God's loving presence.

26:22.023 --> 26:22.965
All of us deserve that.

26:24.127 --> 26:25.208
That's the problem of sin.

26:26.029 --> 26:31.578
But the provision, the provision of a Savior is where God intervenes.

26:32.279 --> 26:34.943
And God's grace and His mercy and His love.

26:36.345 --> 26:42.194
Romans chapter 5 verse 8, but God demonstrates His love in this while we were still sinners.

26:42.626 --> 26:43.787
Christ died for us.

26:44.588 --> 26:47.472
As I mentioned before, Jesus Christ is the Lamb of God.

26:48.113 --> 26:50.275
He was born to die.

26:51.296 --> 26:57.764
From the very beginning, the Garden of Eden, from Adam and Eve's very first act of disobedience brought sin into the universe.

26:58.164 --> 27:09.618
From the very beginning to the ultimate end when God creates a whole new heaven and earth, all of it revolves around Jesus Christ and his sacrifice on the cross.

27:10.146 --> 27:16.576
For all history before that, all the animal sacrifice in the Old Testament, they were all pointing to the cross.

27:17.197 --> 27:18.258
Why we take communion?

27:18.879 --> 27:20.562
We're gonna, next Sunday, we're serving the communion.

27:20.982 --> 27:23.787
These elements point back to the cross.

27:24.468 --> 27:31.659
All of human history revolves around the death of Jesus Christ, the sacrifice of Jesus on the cross.

27:32.320 --> 27:34.603
He was the provision from God.

27:34.623 --> 27:39.090
Where there's a problem of sin that separates us from God, the wages of sin is death,

27:39.618 --> 27:45.127
But the provision of God is His only Son who died for our sin.

27:46.289 --> 27:53.822
Problem of sin, provision of a Savior, third and crucial step, personal decision.

27:54.743 --> 27:56.546
Everybody's got to make a personal decision.

27:57.508 --> 28:06.162
And in the world today, there have been for thousands of years, have always taught this thing called universalism, which means everybody's going to heaven.

28:06.434 --> 28:07.796
All roads lead to heaven.

28:07.816 --> 28:08.717
Doesn't matter what you believe.

28:08.737 --> 28:09.618
You could be an atheist.

28:09.778 --> 28:10.820
You're still going to heaven.

28:11.581 --> 28:13.723
That's a somewhat common teaching.

28:13.783 --> 28:14.945
It sounds really nice.

28:15.005 --> 28:17.769
I mean, it makes people feel good stuff, but it's not true.

28:17.829 --> 28:20.812
Not everybody's going to heaven.

28:20.833 --> 28:22.715
John 3 16 makes that so clear.

28:23.015 --> 28:26.960
John 3 16, the most well-known Bible verse in the entire world.

28:27.361 --> 28:34.450
Hopefully, we all know it by heart now, but for God so loved the world that he gave his one and only son

28:35.298 --> 28:42.087
that whoever believes in Him should not perish, but have everlasting life.

28:42.107 --> 28:45.831
The condition of any gift is to personally receive it.

28:46.612 --> 28:49.996
Someone offers you us the greatest gift in the world and we say, ah, no thanks.

28:51.018 --> 28:52.840
We're not gonna enjoy the benefit of that gift.

28:52.920 --> 28:54.202
We have to personally receive it.

28:55.123 --> 28:59.969
So there's the problem of sin, there's a provision of a Savior, but there's a personal decision.

29:00.630 --> 29:03.954
We need to put our faith and trust in Jesus Christ.

29:04.642 --> 29:13.651
And you've heard me say it before, one of the scariest things for a lot of ministers, especially in America, is thinking about people who were literally born into a good church.

29:13.671 --> 29:17.515
I mean, like generationally, their families has always been in a good church.

29:17.535 --> 29:26.804
They've heard the gospel thousands of times, and yet they may perhaps have never personally trusted in Christ.

29:27.945 --> 29:30.688
They think they're like environmental Christians.

29:30.908 --> 29:32.850
They're Christians because of the environment.

29:34.594 --> 29:35.595
doesn't work like that.

29:36.776 --> 29:44.844
God has a personal direct relationship with each and every person, but that only happens when that person puts their faith in trust in Jesus Christ.

29:45.585 --> 29:51.710
Now, we believe that a three or four year old can understand enough to believe in Jesus Christ as their Lord and Savior.

29:52.451 --> 29:53.732
Say, well, what if they're younger than that?

29:53.832 --> 30:00.539
Well, I had a sermon on that, but different beliefs, but personally, I believe if there's an age of accountability.

30:00.559 --> 30:03.762
I mean, if you're not even consciously able to process

30:04.002 --> 30:10.390
what the gospel is, or who God is, and respond positively or negatively to the existence of God.

30:11.331 --> 30:13.994
Then you're going to have it, okay, when you die.

30:14.034 --> 30:15.536
I mean, that's just my own personal belief.

30:15.556 --> 30:16.577
There's some scriptures about it.

30:17.138 --> 30:27.370
But once you become consciously able to choose to believe in God or not, and that's a pretty young age, three or four, things start getting the concept of a higher being.

30:28.191 --> 30:30.354
What's their personal decision?

30:30.786 --> 30:33.109
And that's why having kids programs are so important.

30:33.129 --> 30:34.291
We do vacation Bible school.

30:34.311 --> 30:37.335
I appreciate those who help out with vacation Bible school every year.

30:38.257 --> 30:45.447
And those who help with all of our children's ministries, Sunday school, children's church, little three or four year olds.

30:45.527 --> 30:46.889
Sometimes they say, yeah, they're just little kids.

30:48.151 --> 30:50.354
I don't know how many adults I've talked to over the years.

30:50.695 --> 30:52.477
You say, well, when did you first come to faith in Christ?

30:52.677 --> 30:56.783
They can't remember exactly, but they do remember it was very, very young.

30:56.803 --> 30:58.706
Maybe they were blessed to be in a Christian home.

30:59.362 --> 31:05.169
Maybe they went to a vacation Bible school or a Sunday school program somewhere, because somebody took them.

31:06.050 --> 31:09.014
And that's when they first trusted in Christ when they were just three or four years old.

31:09.995 --> 31:13.619
But if we're here today, again, so the question is not how long have you been in church?

31:14.220 --> 31:16.002
Or how much religious stuff do we do?

31:16.603 --> 31:17.664
Do you read your Bible every day?

31:17.724 --> 31:18.545
Do you pray every day?

31:18.565 --> 31:19.086
Do you give?

31:19.106 --> 31:19.566
Do you serve?

31:19.807 --> 31:22.129
Those are all wonderful things for Christians to do.

31:22.950 --> 31:25.934
But that's not how you become a Christian.

31:26.675 --> 31:29.298
We become a Christian through our own personal faith

31:29.762 --> 31:30.763
in Jesus Christ.

31:31.264 --> 31:32.525
Do we believe he's the Son of God?

31:33.106 --> 31:34.428
Do we believe he died for my sin?

31:35.088 --> 31:37.051
And do I believe he was raised from the dead?

31:38.192 --> 31:42.037
Problem of sin, provision of a savior, personal decision.

31:43.238 --> 31:55.954
This is something I've been here almost 10 years, but you know, and I haven't done this very often, and I probably should have done it more often, but when I close in prayer after this message, the all heads bowed and eyes closed.

31:55.974 --> 31:59.538
I'm gonna ask if anybody wants to talk about this

31:59.970 --> 32:04.115
after church, because they're not sure, just to raise their hand.

32:04.856 --> 32:17.972
Without people looking around, this is just private, this is personal, being us and God, but I'm gonna ask you to raise your hand, and I'm gonna look for you, and then after church, if you don't wanna raise your hand, because you're too embarrassed, whatever, that's okay.

32:17.992 --> 32:29.906
But you know, later, today, after we're dismissed, please let me know, or if you have another church leader here that you trust, or have a relationship with, talk to them, and ask them, say, hey,

32:30.050 --> 32:34.435
You know, I'm not sure whether I've been in church all my life or where this is my first time.

32:34.475 --> 32:35.256
It doesn't matter.

32:36.077 --> 32:41.003
What matters is, do I know Jesus Christ as my Lord and Savior today.

32:42.505 --> 32:42.865
Okay.

32:42.886 --> 32:49.013
So we're going to close in prayer and I'm going to ask that everybody would please bow your heads, close your eyes.

32:49.974 --> 32:53.078
Everybody right now, everybody just bow our heads, close your eyes.

32:53.819 --> 32:55.100
Nobody is looking around.

32:55.941 --> 32:56.562
Please.

32:57.442 --> 32:58.864
Let's respect everybody's privacy.

32:58.884 --> 33:01.847
Let's just bow our heads, close our eyes, everybody.

33:02.828 --> 33:04.470
Bow our heads, close our eyes.

33:06.312 --> 33:08.175
I'm the only one looking around it right now, okay?

33:10.037 --> 33:17.686
Father God, you know what's in our hearts and you know whether we've been in church, all our lives are not.

33:18.947 --> 33:24.594
You know as we know whether or not we have ever put our faith in trust

33:24.770 --> 33:27.493
in Jesus Christ as our own personal Lord and Savior.

33:28.534 --> 33:41.706
And so right now, if there's anyone here today who's not sure, and you would like to talk about it later today or sometime this week or whenever it's convenient for you, would you just raise your hand right now?

33:42.927 --> 33:44.629
Just slip up your hand for a moment.

33:44.669 --> 33:48.893
Nobody looking around, okay, I see that one hand, all right, you can put your hand out.

33:49.574 --> 33:50.114
Anybody else?

33:51.595 --> 33:54.258
Just slip your hand up for a moment, okay?

33:55.042 --> 33:55.903
Let's continue praying.

33:56.985 --> 34:02.873
Father, if there is someone else who's not sure here this morning, they were uncomfortable about raising their hand.

34:03.013 --> 34:03.554
That's fine.

34:04.375 --> 34:18.093
But Father, I pray that your spirit would work in their heart and their life, cause them to have a curiosity and a concern that would motivate them to talk to somebody as soon as possible.

34:19.315 --> 34:22.980
And Father, perhaps there's someone else here today who has heard the gospel before.

34:23.000 --> 34:24.562
They understand it very well.

34:25.314 --> 34:28.779
And they have just never put their faith and trust in you for whatever reason.

34:28.819 --> 34:32.044
And maybe this would be the day of salvation for them.

34:32.124 --> 34:38.935
Right now, I pray that they would pray that simple prayer in their heart for you.

34:38.955 --> 34:49.871
So not a matter of how eloquent our words are, but to simply express from their heart that they believe that Jesus is your son, that he died for our sin, and that he rose from the dead.

34:50.672 --> 34:54.418
And right now they trust in him as their own Lord and Savior.

34:55.074 --> 34:57.899
Father, if there's someone that's prayed that prayer, we rejoice together.

34:58.700 --> 35:03.388
But I pray that they would pursue what it means to grow in the Christian life.

35:04.129 --> 35:10.420
That becoming a Christian is only the beginning of a whole new relationship with you that involves growth.

35:11.222 --> 35:18.514
That they'll make a church, a church that you will lead them to that will help them to get into your word

35:18.882 --> 35:24.876
to be in prayer, communication with you, and fellowship with other Christians to be involved in ministry and serving others.

35:25.658 --> 35:27.201
And so Father, we thank you for this morning.

35:27.823 --> 35:31.311
We'll give you all the praise and thanks for it in Jesus' name we pray.

35:32.213 --> 35:32.594
Amen.

